# 📢 Subnet Update Announcement – March 17, 2025

Hey Miners @deleted-role 

We’ll be rolling out a simple subnet update today at 4:00 PM UTC. Here’s what’s changing:

🔹 Bittensor Version Upgrade to 9.1.0
This update aims to keep the subnet API alive and address the issue where zero-axon miners were still receiving incentives. These problems started after upgrading to BT version 9.0.0, and we’re hopeful this fix will resolve them. Please update your subnet version in time

## 🚀 Major Update to Incentive Mechanism(v.2.5.0) – March 18, 2025

We’re excited to introduce significant improvements to the incentive mechanism to ensure a fairer and more reliable network. Here’s what’s coming:

🔹 Integration of Anthropic Claude for Image-to-Text Validation
* We’re introducing Anthropic Claude to validate the accuracy of rendered images by comparing them with their respective prompts. This will enhance the evaluation process to how well the prompts is reflected to 3D model

🔹 Standardized Preview Images Across Miners
* Preview images will now be normalized for all miners within the same batch. This ensures that all miners compete under the same conditions.
* Additionally, all images will be converted to .jpeg format, resized to 200x200 pixels, and optimized for compatibility with Claude.

🔹 Penalty for Low Processing Miners
* Miners handling fewer requests will now receive a penalty score, encouraging a more balanced workload across the network.

🔹 Increased Validator Request Interval

* Validator request intervals will increase to 700 seconds to allow miners to process more organic requests.
* Future incentives will reward miners who handle organic requests efficiently.

## 🛠️ Testnet Validator Update

* The testnet validator (UID 3) will start running with new updates by the end of today. Will let you know.
* We plan to merge these changes on March 18, 2025, at 6:00 PM UTC.
Please test your miner on the testnet and report any issues.
Thanks for your support!
